Connect Django Backend on Azure to GitHub (CI/CD)
1. Push Your Django Project to GitHub
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/your-django-repo.git
git push -u origin main

2. Create an Azure Web App
az login
az webapp up --name your-django-backend-app --runtime "PYTHON|3.10" --location "East US"

3. Set up Deployment from Github
https://portal.azure.com/#home
Navigate to your Web App
    On the left panel, go to Deployment Center
Choose:
    Source: GitHub
    Build provider: GitHub Actions
    Repository & Branch: Select your repo and branch
Azure will auto-generate a GitHub Actions workflow for Django.

4. Migrate MySQL database to Microsoft Azure cloud service
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uxSDpZnFa18
- Create a new Azure MySQL database
- Open MySQL Workbench and migrate
Database tab -> Migration Wizard

5. Connect a Django project to a MySQL database hosted on Azure, and retrieve data in JSON format,
From index.html, link to orders.html
From orders.html, fetch data
Step 1: Set Up MySQL on Azure
Step 2: Install MySQL Client for Django
Step 3: Configure settings.py in Django
Step 4: Use Django ORM to Query and Convert to JSON (in views.py)
Step 5: Sends MySQL data as JSON to the frontend.
Step 6: Wire the View to a URL (in urls.py)
Step 7: Call the Endpoint from the Frontend (in React or plain JS)

Error: ERROR 2002 (HY000): Can't connect to local MySQL server through socket '/tmp/mysql.sock' (2)
Reason: mysqld_safe (check location by "which mysqld_safe")
Solution: brew services start mysql

Step 8: Query database (adding)
MySQL CLI Connection Command
mysql -h django-education-mysql.mysql.database.azure.com -u chinguyen@ydjango-education-mysql -p -D all_orders_db
-> ERROR
OR if SSL is required (Azure often require SSL)
mysql --host=django-education-mysql.mysql.database.azure.com --user=chinguyen@ydjango-education-mysql --password --ssl-mode=REQUIRED --database=all_orders_db
-> ERROR
mysql --host=django-education-mysql.mysql.database.azure.com \
      --user=chinguyen@django-education-mysql \
      --password \
      --database=all_orders_db \
      --ssl-ca=/path/to/BaltimoreCyberTrustRoot.crt.pem
-> ERROR
-> Solution: download SSL cert

Can disable SSL check for testing

Enable SSL:
- download SSL: 
    curl -O https://www.digicert.com/CACerts/BaltimoreCyberTrustRoot.crt.pem
    brew install openssl
    openssl genpkey -algorithm RSA -out client-key.pem
    openssl req -new -x509 -key client-key.pem -out client-cert.pem -days 365

Reset MySQL Workbench root password:
    sql> 
    USE mysql;
    ALTER USER 'root'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'your_new_password';
    EXIT;
    brew services restart mysql
    mysql -u root -p

Check version of mysqlclient and PyMySQL
    pip list | grep -i 'mysql'

ERROR: an unexpected keyword argument 'ssl_ca'
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/troubleshoot/mem/configmgr/setup-migrate-backup-recovery/connectivity-issues-digicert-global-root-g2-not-installed
-> TRY:
'ssl': {
                'ca': '/path/to/DigiCertGlobalRootG2.crt.pem',  # Path to the CA certificate
                'cert': '/path/to/client-cert.pem',  # Path to the client certificate
                'key': '/path/to/client-key.pem',    # Path to the client key
            },

-> SOLVED

After solving problem, because changed in models, makemigrations and migrate
ERROR: (migrate)

ERROR: connect to Azure remote database
mysql> ALTER USER 'root'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED WITH mysql_native_password BY 'password123';FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
